 * "description":"<i>Women Spies: A Novel of Remembrance of Mata Hari, Mary Bowser, Noor Inayat Khan, Nancy Wake and other Strong Women of History<\/i> is a historical fiction that uses the \"grandmother's chair\" method to recount the very real histories of famous and infamous female spies down through the ages. The story begins with Lannie (a fictitious character) watching a mysterious neighbor moving in next door. Her grandmother (also fictitious) collects stories about spies. As Lannie learns about famous female spies, so does the listener. The fictitious background is used as a vehicle for discussing each of the featured women, presenting various views, some of them opposing, that affect our perception of these women today. A <i>Forbes Magazine<\/i> article commented that women have always been uniquely suited to spying because they understand subtle messages delivered through body language, and because they understand how people interact. The article goes on to say that women are good at multitasking, as a rule, since it is often required for successfully running a home. These are just a few of the traits needed to be a successful spy. The book also touches on spies for the other side, and has a running thread of plot that focuses around the fictional characters."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1563993541, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"The Ottoman Empire: The Untold Story to its Rise and Fall Plus the Revolutionary War: The Making of America Bundle (2 Books in 1) (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"The Ottoman Empire: The Untold Story to its Rise and Fall Plus the Revolutionary War: The Making of America Bundle (2 Books in 1) (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/the-ottoman-empire-the-untold-story-to-its-rise-and/id1563993541?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music115/v4/01/7d/08/017d089f-b65b-adc0-b652-76601302d446/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music115/v4/01/7d/08/017d089f-b65b-adc0-b652-76601302d446/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":17.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2024 We Cant Be Beat LLC", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2024-08-04T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"History",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview115/v4/3f/ee/11/3fee1106-b76f-6f05-cc98-c6c1978e46f8/mzaf_2298507114672249995.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"In times of great strife, history is made. History aficionados recognize the importance of the major events and the significance of the often underreported or little-known events that impacted lives, cemented beliefs, changed the course of history, and left indelible impressions on those who bore witness to these events.<br /><br /><i>The Ottoman Empire: The Untold Story to its Rise and Fall Plus the Revolutionary War: The Making of America (2 Books in 1) <\/i>brings that history and the life-changing accounts to life. This two-book bundle takes a deep dive into the everyday lives of colonists, explores the upheaval and rebellions that shaped the lives of those who were there and for generations to come, the stronghold the Ottoman Empire had on the world, the origins of its storied population and how they came to power, the contributions they made, the great changes that occurred as a result of the Revolutionary War in America, and the secrets history books won’t tell you.&#xa0;<br /><br />Inside, you’ll discover:<br />\nWhy The Revolutionary War began\nThe rise and fall of the Ottoman Empire\nPhases of the war and why they’re significant\nThe role sultans played in the great battles of the Ottoman Empire\nThe consequences of battle in the Ottoman Empire and the Revolutionary War\nThe stories behind&#xa0;\nCosts of war\nProminent figure heads, leaders, rebels, and fighters\n\n<br />Expand your knowledge. Discover how battles from so long ago impact our lives now and learn about important events in history with this two-book bundle."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1190359698, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"Ulysses S. Grant: The Forgotten Hero (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"Ulysses S. Grant: The Forgotten Hero (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/ulysses-s-grant-the-forgotten-hero-unabridged/id1190359698?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music122/v4/42/30/d0/4230d023-d335-6160-49fa-29bc19c3cfb3/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music122/v4/42/30/d0/4230d023-d335-6160-49fa-29bc19c3cfb3/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":12.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2016 Jack Johnson", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2016-12-16T08:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Biographies & Memoirs",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/7e/79/44/7e794416-d892-38e2-9046-0f9b6ecaa57f/mzaf_3467366892916064761.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"You might know Ulysses S. Grant as a Civil War hero and as the 18th president of the United States, but we will introduce you to the heart and soul of the man who brought freedom and equality to a troubled America. Within this book, you'll discover how Grant motivated and inspired a nation to rise above the dark days of slavery and financial ruin and search their hearts for justice for all. You'll battle with Grant and his men at Vicksburg, and be there when General Lee surrenders at Appomattox. <br /><br />When the Civil War ends, you'll travel with Grant out West to settle the Native Americans, and you'll experience \"Custer's Last Stand\". You'll share in Grant's epic victories and colossal failures as he serves as president of the United States. Your heart will be broken as you hear about the devastating disease that finally took his life only three days after he completed his memoirs. As the funeral procession passes through the streets of New York, you'll be there with the millions of people to pay their respects to one of the greatest leaders of his time. <br /><br />When you have finished, you can look at the America you live in today and ask yourself if you are strong enough and determined enough to promote the ideas, beliefs, and values that were initiated by Ulysses S. Grant."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1051859430, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"Job Interview: Job Interview Success, Get a Job, Interview, Always Succeed & Influence (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"Job Interview: Job Interview Success, Get a Job, Interview, Always Succeed & Influence (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/job-interview-job-interview-success-get-a-job/id1051859430?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music221/v4/5c/dd/44/5cdd449b-0cdf-3698-1d1b-2ff36dd6c39a/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music221/v4/5c/dd/44/5cdd449b-0cdf-3698-1d1b-2ff36dd6c39a/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":5.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2015 Zac", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2015-10-07T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Business & Personal Finance",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview123/v4/8c/f3/d0/8cf3d03b-bfee-75f7-bafc-1be97883d4d4/mzaf_887730273485770857.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"Have you ever felt nervous before a job interview because you didn't know what the interviewer was going to say? Are you struggling to find a job in a world that is moving so fast? Would you like to learn the secrets to getting yourself an interview and being able to show up with confidence? <br /><br />I wrote this audiobook for anyone who wants to find a job, land a job, and have an advantage over other people. I have spent the last decade learning and helping people like you find jobs and land them. I used to apply for 10 jobs at a time just for an experiment because I wanted to know the secrets and the patterns, so you know what to prepare for. <br /><br />We feel anxious before most job interviews because it's complete uncertainty, and we don't know the techniques to feel confident. I will show you the right mind-set you need to land your ideal job and give you a list of the most common questions that the interviewer will ask you. You will learn how to become more confident within yourself and how to build rapport with the interviewer, so you will stand out. This whole game is about standing out of the pack, and I will give you all the ways to make it happen - all you need to do is apply it, and you'll have the job you're looking for. <br /><br /><b>Take action today and get that job you've always wanted.<\/b>"},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1038258385, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"Depression: Stop Dying & Start Living: Social Anxiety, Insecurities, Fear,  & Depression Cure (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"Depression: Stop Dying & Start Living: Social Anxiety, Insecurities, Fear,  & Depression Cure (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/depression-stop-dying-start-living-social-anxiety-insecurities/id1038258385?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music3/v4/86/71/25/8671255d-94f6-6945-7703-d67ff7cf1119/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music3/v4/86/71/25/8671255d-94f6-6945-7703-d67ff7cf1119/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":5.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2015 Zac Dixon", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2015-08-26T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Business & Personal Finance",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/da/46/a9/da46a942-a958-e815-4272-278b1b7cde13/mzaf_3517794415109790326.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"Depression is a negative emotion that can lead to suicide or freedom. So many people in this world struggle with this emotion, and every human experiences this sooner or later. The difference is some know how to break out of it and turn their lives into something great, whereas others will hold on to it because of their addiction to it. <br /><br />We all get addicted to our emotions, and if we can understand this, we have real power to change it. I want to give you a new way of thinking because I have personally struggled for years with depression, and I know the simple secrets that got me out of that place. I help people through my seminars and through coaching, and I see the patterns with everyone. I know how to turn them around, but they have to want to change. <br /><br />The truth is,you can live your ideal life if you see the big picture of where you're heading. We're always rationalizing that \"someday I'll be happy\", and someday never comes. Today is your day to wake up and start living with purpose, and I'll show you the secret formula to get you there. <br /><br />Take action today, and let's beat this depression once and for all."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1427820018, "collectionId":1441509207, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson & Jack Gilinsky", "collectionName":"Jack & Jack: You Don't Know Jacks", "collectionCensoredName":"Jack & Jack: You Don't Know Jacks", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1427820018?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/jack-jack-you-dont-know-jacks/id1441509207?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music118/v4/13/d0/d5/13d0d5a5-347d-0cb4-a170-4846e46065d0/9780062570154.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music118/v4/13/d0/d5/13d0d5a5-347d-0cb4-a170-4846e46065d0/9780062570154.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":6.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2016-09-06T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Kids & Young Adults",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/0a/fd/2e/0afd2e4e-82f8-7d83-96e6-93b4ca99a533/mzaf_7585685808789146885.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"Vine ingenues, YouTube megastars, hip-pop sensations, and best friends Jack &amp; Jack bring their own brand of irreverent comedy, on-point style, and heartfelt life advice to You Don't Know Jacks.<br /><br />Nebraska natives Jack Gilinsky and Jack Johnson shot to instant fame after their first Vine, \"\"Nerd Vandals,\"\" was dubbed \"\"a perfect Vine\"\" by the Huffington Post. It's been looped more than ten million times since—and that Vine was just the beginning.<br /><br />Now, after a number one hit on iTunes, nearly two million singles sold, live performances where they have shared the stage with Demi Lovato, Shawn Mendes, and Fifth Harmony, and over 26 million followers across all their social media channels, Jack &amp; Jack are on a wild ride—and they're not planning to slow down anytime soon.<br /><br />Fans will love listening about their journey from being two regular kids growing up in Omaha, Nebraska, to global superstardom. Complete with behind-the-scenes stories and hilarious personal anecdotes, You Don't Know Jacks is an insider look at the lives of Jack &amp; Jack, as told by the guys themselves."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1079567910, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"The Revolutionary War: The Making of America: An Introduction to the People, the Ideas, and the Major Events of the American Revolution (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"The Revolutionary War: The Making of America: An Introduction to the People, the Ideas, and the Major Events of the American Revolution (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/the-revolutionary-war-the-making-of-america/id1079567910?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music49/v4/cf/e8/2c/cfe82c92-46e5-19f5-b38e-5d00f81037b5/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music49/v4/cf/e8/2c/cfe82c92-46e5-19f5-b38e-5d00f81037b5/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":5.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2016 WE CANT BE BEAT LLC", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2016-01-21T08:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"History",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/99/c4/84/99c48467-71dd-0a95-8388-3c5d4d433ee2/mzaf_6642611679343132363.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"<i>The Revolutionary War: The Making of America<\/i> retells the story of the American Revolution in a way that captures your attention and is as educational as it is entertaining. This book covers the events of the American Revolution, but also their cultural and historical significance. This book also overviews the most important players on both sides of the conflict, and pays special attention to the key figures who led this military and political struggle and went on to found the American republic."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1147836664, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"The Ottoman Empire: The Untold Story to Its Rise and Fall (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"The Ottoman Empire: The Untold Story to Its Rise and Fall (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/the-ottoman-empire-the-untold-story-to-its-rise/id1147836664?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music71/v4/3a/a0/2d/3aa02d4c-0cb4-286e-1aa6-b720da614080/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music71/v4/3a/a0/2d/3aa02d4c-0cb4-286e-1aa6-b720da614080/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":12.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2024 WE CANT BE BEAT LLC", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2024-11-08T08:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"History",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview116/v4/3f/2e/fe/3f2efefa-a677-6810-0859-4023a390263e/mzaf_16806452609253068688.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"The Ottoman Empire was a strong world power for over 600 years beginning in the late 13th century. How did it rise from one man who was given charge of a small parcel of land to an empire that spanned three continents? Why did it begin to lose battle after battle, eventually reaching a point where it was beaten back by its enemies? Which sultans presented the empire with the tools for success and which destroyed the unity? What contributed to its demise? <br /><br />These questions and more will be answered through this book as the secrets of the Ottoman Empire are revealed. This book contains a description of the origins and basics about the population of citizens within the empire along with descriptions about each of the 36 emperors' personal rises and falls in their quest to better the empire. Additionally, the contributions the Ottomans made to their empire and beyond to other countries will be described along with the daily life of those within the palace and those without. Is there anything left today that came from the Ottoman Empire? Or did the Ottoman Empire simply disappear without a trace left to indicate it existed?"},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1088429617, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson",
 * "collectionName":"Abraham Lincoln - 'Honest Abe': The Life and Times of the Man Who Led America Through Its Greatest Moral, Political, and Constitutional Crisis (Unabridged)",
 * "collectionCensoredName":"Abraham Lincoln - 'Honest Abe': The Life and Times of the Man Who Led America Through Its Greatest Moral, Political, and Constitutional Crisis (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/abraham-lincoln-honest-abe-the-life-and-times-of-the/id1088429617?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music49/v4/ab/e3/ef/abe3efd7-977a-a5c6-d74f-1b049741f1cc/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music49/v4/ab/e3/ef/abe3efd7-977a-a5c6-d74f-1b049741f1cc/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":5.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2016 WE CANT BE BEAT LLC", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2016-02-22T08:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Biographies & Memoirs",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/48/45/16/48451665-2dec-fc36-2b56-ba7b539e158f/mzaf_4691711533170477284.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"<i>Honest Abe<\/i> was written to act as your easy reference point that contains everything you need to know about the life and times of Abraham Lincoln. Throughout the book, I have sought to paint the picture of the scenes I describe, so that this is more than an academic treatise. This book is meant to be more of a movie; a movie that plays out in your head as you hear its vivid details, so that you can feel that you were there as it was happening. <br /><br />This is certainly a quick listen, but it is densely packed with information that so many historians tend to overlook. Lincoln's story is a gripping tale, from beginning to end. Given the massive nature of his accomplishments and the nearly six decades he lived, you might wonder how these words can adequately cover so much ground. This book will give you an excellent grasp of the man - as a son, as a younger brother, as a father, as a thinker, as a politician, and, of course, as our 16th president."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1110998841, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"Growing Up During the Cold War: A Personal Perspective from the Forties to Today (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"Growing Up During the Cold War: A Personal Perspective from the Forties to Today (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/growing-up-during-the-cold-war-a-personal/id1110998841?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music60/v4/6e/08/97/6e0897cf-e306-adde-c972-66e42d5c1966/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music60/v4/6e/08/97/6e0897cf-e306-adde-c972-66e42d5c1966/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":12.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2024 WE CANT BE BEAT LLC", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2024-11-06T08:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Biographies & Memoirs",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/90/ad/bc/90adbc29-c3be-fea2-9a17-1d808ed03646/mzaf_7520320847665991848.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"<i>Growing up during The Cold War: A Personal Perspective from the Forties to Today<\/i> relates in narrative form the tumultuous, exciting and sometimes frightening era referred to as the Cold War Era. Civil Rights, Women's Lib, Anti-War Drafts and changes in the educational system all characterized the times. Told from the point of view of some of those who lived in the central part of the United States, far from the conflict and even decently distant from the unrest in urban centers, it is an effort to portray both the uncertainty and the wonder as exploration of space both within and without was mood of the times. <br /><br />Such a work cannot replace the experience of living through those times. And, no doubt, since any writer must pick and choose between events that occur in such times, there are things that have been left out of this account. However, it can serve as a springboard for those who wish to explore this recent history and it places a variety of sources into a coherent timeline of events and changes. It is not limited to conflict, but also embraces advances spurred on by the rivalry between the United States and Soviet Russia. Landmark changes occurred in the United States legal system, as well."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1127481158, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"Ambition Without Boundaries: How Julius Caesar's Thirst for Conquest Shaped the Ancient World, and Impacted the Modern One (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"Ambition Without Boundaries: How Julius Caesar's Thirst for Conquest Shaped the Ancient World, and Impacted the Modern One (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/ambition-without-boundaries-how-julius-caesars-thirst/id1127481158?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music60/v4/eb/22/c4/eb22c4b4-c94e-5a47-1b69-caddf84337bb/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music60/v4/eb/22/c4/eb22c4b4-c94e-5a47-1b69-caddf84337bb/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":12.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2016 WE CANT BE BEAT LLC", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2016-06-17T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Biographies & Memoirs",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview123/v4/53/45/6e/53456ed7-1033-83bc-b01a-5a3fa1186665/mzaf_1185154278098523116.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"This biography on one of history's most storied figures takes listeners on an exciting journey through the detailed history of Julius Caesar. Julius Caesar was a man who influenced the world in unparalleled ways, and his story is one loaded with an extravagant cast of politicians, generals, and royalty. It makes for a riveting tale of intrigue and melodrama. <br /><br />The audiobook begins with Caesar's early life, and the humble background from which he came. His accounts of great triumphs and great defeats are all included, as his exciting and eventful life is traced through the minutes of the book. Caesar was part of a time where record keeping was incredibly proficient, and the pieces we have to put together the life of this man and those around him are plentiful. Caesar's story is important down to the last detail, and this book encapsulates the details that matter, and help paint a picture of this legendary figure and the tumultuous time in which he lived. <br /><br />The greatest forms of entertainment can be found in the truth, rather than fiction, and Caesar's life is proof of this. It is history that tells us the most extravagant and unbelievable stories. No matter what amount of speculation or conjecture you throw into this story, the impact of Caesar's life is undeniable. His legacy is one that must be heard, and all that you could want to know about the man lies within this audiobook."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1036384314, "collectionId":1115795741, "amgArtistId":468749, "artistName":"Jack Johnson", "collectionName":"John Adams: Revealing Relationships of a Founding Father (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"John Adams: Revealing Relationships of a Founding Father (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/jack-johnson/id1036384314?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/john-adams-revealing-relationships-of-a/id1115795741?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music18/v4/f2/5f/0c/f25f0c86-4b64-d10c-8239-b4e060eacdfb/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music18/v4/f2/5f/0c/f25f0c86-4b64-d10c-8239-b4e060eacdfb/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":5.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2016 WE CANT BE BEAT LLC", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2016-05-12T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Biographies & Memoirs",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview123/v4/f6/4a/b9/f64ab98e-f9ed-58f7-1c0f-87b0abda9904/mzaf_8138785711425810399.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"John Adams didn't cut a dashing figure like George Washington. He was not the darling of France, as was Benjamin Franklin. He was not a wealthy and statuesque plantation owner like Thomas Jefferson. Adams was highly opinionated, blunt, and often tactless in his social interactions. To top it off, he was short, fat, and awkward. This does not sound like the description of a Founding Father we should want to know any better - but that's where you're wrong. <br /><br />Adams, perhaps more than any other Founding Father, was a driving force that pushed America to declare its independence from Britain. It was Adams who supplied the raw ideas of what a new government should look like. He always represented the larger public good in all of his public service, even when buffeted by the forces of antagonistic party politics during his tenure as the second president of the United States. The details and legacy of his life's work are best viewed through the lens of his relationships with people, places, and ideas. <br /><br />In <i>John Adams: Revealing Relationships of a Founding Father<\/i>, you will learn how Adams was frustrated with France, jostled by Jefferson, aided by Abigail and flummoxed by Franklin as well as how he masterminded his son's success in politics with Monroe and was often perplexed by politics."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":44051403, "collectionId":1437534186, "amgArtistId":3239043, "artistName":"Judy Johnson", "collectionName":"Jack (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"Jack (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/judy-johnson/id44051403?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/jack-unabridged/id1437534186?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music128/v4/a5/35/5e/a5355e33-80d5-9976-aac8-d47d3d426490/9781742016191_FrontCover_Trade_DD.jpg/60x60bb.jpg",
 * "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music128/v4/a5/35/5e/a5355e33-80d5-9976-aac8-d47d3d426490/9781742016191_FrontCover_Trade_DD.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":19.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2007 Bolinda Publishing", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2010-05-14T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Fiction",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/c9/1f/cb/c91fcb84-dea8-5a34-d61e-2c2a9fc6db62/mzaf_2537336369224680704.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"One-eyed Jack Falconer is a man with many secrets...\n\nIt's 1938, the eve of World War II, and a pearling lugger in the Torres Strait is the place he chooses to hide. But Jack's demons follow him out to sea and rise to the surface just as surely as the pearl shell his divers collect from the dangers of the deep. Embittered, intelligent and self-destructive, Jack's only way to prove himself is to compete with, defeat and destroy the very weaknesses he fears.\n\nSet in the expansive and beautiful Coral Sea, Jack's provocative tale of a dangerous captain and his young crew at odds with the elements - and each other - holds the reader breathless until the very last page."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":76849047, "collectionId":1454430550, "amgArtistId":899462, "artistName":"Charles R. Smith Jr.", "collectionName":"Black Jack: The Ballad of Jack Johnson", "collectionCensoredName":"Black Jack: The Ballad of Jack Johnson", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/charles-r-smith-jr/id76849047?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/black-jack-the-ballad-of-jack-johnson/id1454430550?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music124/v4/cd/3f/1f/cd3f1f3b-de53-8f79-52dc-22a84f8b01bd/9781430115175_1_cover.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music124/v4/cd/3f/1f/cd3f1f3b-de53-8f79-52dc-22a84f8b01bd/9781430115175_1_cover.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":9.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2011 Live Oak Media", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2011-01-01T08:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Kids & Young Adults",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview115/v4/c9/50/93/c9509320-5da7-dc49-c5ff-9e6991853022/mzaf_6039512440829169622.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"A powerful telling of the first African-American heavyweight champion, this story portrays how a shy, fearful young man learned to fight back and become one of history's more compelling personalities."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":366169796, "collectionId":1225756959, "artistName":"Samuel Williams", "collectionName":"Anomalous: The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes Featuring Jack Johnson and Alphonse Capone (Unabridged)", "collectionCensoredName":"Anomalous: The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes Featuring Jack Johnson and Alphonse Capone (Unabridged)", "artistViewUrl":"https://music.apple.com/us/artist/samuel-williams/366169796?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/anomalous-the-adventures-of-sherlock-holmes/id1225756959?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music122/v4/c8/d2/59/c8d25991-2eac-9ef9-c71c-9b9eae17a2b4/rm_image.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music122/v4/c8/d2/59/c8d25991-2eac-9ef9-c71c-9b9eae17a2b4/rm_image.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":17.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "copyright":"© 2017 MX Publishing", "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2017-04-05T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Nonfiction",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview113/v4/1f/ee/0e/1fee0e97-1e87-18d8-42f7-346c6cc76e80/mzaf_9106454356569490188.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"America's first African American heavyweight boxing champion, Jack Johnson, has a chance encounter with a mysterious Irishman, named Altamont, when they meet at the boxer's restaurant, Café de Champion, in August 1912. Johnson's new relationship with the unusual man, with beady eyes and hawk-like nose, places him in an unusual circumstance to help Altamont get out of a tough situation. <br /><br />In 1913, Johnson is nailed with a felony conviction in the American court system and flees to Canada, and later travels to England, to meet with fight promoters. But a stolen South African 'blood diamond' and a grudge harbored against the controversial boxer from the past, puts Johnson's life in peril while on British soil, reuniting him with the mysterious Altamont. Will Johnson uncover the true identity of this Irishman, and entrust his life to Altamont's care? <br /><br />And as the action unfurls, Johnson forms an alliance with a black British rogue and grifter, Steve Dixie, but can this man be trusted? With all the uncertainty Johnson faces in a foreign land, and for his own protection, he calls in a favor from his American Mafia cronies, finding himself in league with American teenage mobsters, Alphonse Capone, and Frankie Yale. Johnson, Altamont and their entourage of companions' race against the clock, not just to save Johnson's life, but to preserve the national security and future of Britain as well."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1487783791, "collectionId":1704334215, "artistName":"Simon Østergaard Chievitz", "collectionName":"Jack Johnson - Kampen mod politikerne", "collectionCensoredName":"Jack Johnson - Kampen mod politikerne", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/simon-%C3%B8stergaard-chievitz/id1487783791?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/jack-johnson-kampen-mod-politikerne/id1704334215?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music126/v4/20/8f/e3/208fe3e6-6977-0c83-abbd-ddbcf767ec16/9788727115047.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music126/v4/20/8f/e3/208fe3e6-6977-0c83-abbd-ddbcf767ec16/9788727115047.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":1.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2023-09-02T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Nonfiction",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview116/v4/cc/50/9c/cc509c44-d969-43b5-9c1a-26ef5237e6fb/mzaf_5776167450290518871.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"Vi befinder os i USA i 1910'erne, og vi følger stadig bokseren Jack Johnson på hans vej mod berømmelsens tinder. Han er den bedste og mest komplette bokser verden nogensinde har set, og på toppen af sin karriere. Fordi han er det første og største sorte sportsikon USA har set, gør de amerikanske politikere alt for at få ham ned med nakken og genetablere racehierarkiet. Men Jack Johnson giver ikke op uden kamp.\n\nAmerikanerne elsker boksning, og sportens historie er USA's historie. Podcasten '100 års boksning i USA' sætter fokus på de største stjerner og de mest tragiske skæbner - et årti ad gangen. \n\n\nTag med på en rejse gennem USA’s store århundrede og mærk blodet, sveden og tårerne, der har været med til at skabe USA og amerikanerne. Som historien er skredet frem har de amerikanske værdier tæsket løs på hinanden for at finde ud af, hvilke, der skulle være de \"sande\" i USA. Med amerikanernes mest elskede sport som ramme undersøger serien USA’s historie - et årti af gangen - med portrætter af de største stjerner og de mest tragiske skæbner i toppen af amerikansk boksning. Serien sætter spot på race- og klassekampe, kriminalitet og mafia og en buldrende medievirkelighed, der både formidler og forvrænger historien. Serien handler ligeså meget om kultur, politik og samfund som om boksning.\n\nJonas Sølberg er 33 år, freelance journalist og lever af at fortæller historier på tekst, video og podcast. Han er uddannet kandidat i mellemøststudier. Simon Østergaard Chievitz er 29 år, arbejder som konsulent med fokus på politik, organisationer og organisering. Han er uddannet kandidat i idehistorie."},
 * {"wrapperType":"audiobook", "artistId":1487783791, "collectionId":1704334317, "artistName":"Simon Østergaard Chievitz", "collectionName":"Jack Johnson - Den første sorte bokser", "collectionCensoredName":"Jack Johnson - Den første sorte bokser", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/author/simon-%C3%B8stergaard-chievitz/id1487783791?uo=4", "collectionViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/audiobook/jack-johnson-den-f%C3%B8rste-sorte-bokser/id1704334317?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music126/v4/e4/9f/07/e49f07d3-62cf-5617-b94d-f09cc924fb89/9788727115009.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music126/v4/e4/9f/07/e49f07d3-62cf-5617-b94d-f09cc924fb89/9788727115009.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "collectionPrice":1.99, "collectionExplicitness":"cleaned", "trackCount":1, "country":"USA", "currency":"USD", "releaseDate":"2023-09-02T07:00:00Z", "primaryGenreName":"Nonfiction",
 * "previewUrl":"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview116/v4/fc/a0/47/fca047aa-6cf9-39ea-596f-77113492f8ee/mzaf_350061596957808281.std.aac.p.m4a",
 * "description":"Vi befinder os i USA i 1900'erne. Den Amerikanske Borgerkrig har sat slaverne fri i 1865, men USA er stadig delt op i sort og hvid – rige og fattige. Bokseringen bliver en national kampplads, hvor ideologier og politiske overbevisninger kæmper indbyrdes. Den muskuløse kæmpe Jack Johnson tramper, som det første sorte ikon, på samfundets raceskel og tæver de hvide bokseikoner til amerikanernes store forfærdelse.\n\nAmerikanerne elsker boksning, og sportens historie er USA's historie. Podcasten '100 års boksning i USA' sætter fokus på de største stjerner og de mest tragiske skæbner - et årti ad gangen. \n\n\n100 års boksning’ tager dig med på en rejse gennem USA i det 20. århundrede. Mærk blodet, sveden og tårerne, der har været med til at skabe USA og amerikanerne. Gennem amerikanernes mest elskede sport undersøger serien USA’s historie - et årti af gangen - med portrætter af de største stjerner og de mest tragiske skæbner i toppen af amerikansk boksning. Serien sætter spot på race- og klassekampe, kriminalitet og mafia og en buldrende medievirkelighed, der både formidler og forvrænger historien.&#xa0;Værter: Jonas Sølberg, Simon Østergaard Chievitz\n\nJonas Sølberg, freelance journalist og lever af at fortæller historier på tekst, video og podcast. Han er uddannet kandidat i mellemøststudier. Simon Østergaard Chievitz, arbejder som konsulent med fokus på politik, organisationer og organisering. Han er uddannet kandidat i idehistorie."}]
